\sin\theta = \frac{\text{opposite}}{\text{hypotenuse}} = \frac y1 = y
 \cos\theta = \frac{\text{adjacent}}{\text{hypotenuse}} = \frac x 1 = x
(x, y)
(x, y) = (\cos \theta, \sin \theta)
\theta = \frac{\pi}{6} = 30^\circ
y = \sin\left(30^\circ\right) = 1/2
x^2 + y^2 = 1 \iff \cos^2(30^\circ) + \sin(30^\circ) = 1 \iff \cos^2(30) + (1/2)^2 = 1
\iff \cos^2(30) = 3/4 \implies \cos(30) = \sqrt 3/2
